parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to hesitate or lunge forward, leading to loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Transmission slips
shudders
or grinds; hesitation or lunge forward when shifting; failure to accelerate; sudden loss of power; transmission fluid leaks; difficulty shifting into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the torque converter can cause the transmission to slip, leading to loss of power, hesitation, or lunge forward, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Transmission slips or shudders; hesitation or lunge forward when shifting; failure to accelerate; sudden loss of power; transmission fluid leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the vehicle to accelerate properly can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle hesitates or fails to accelerate; sudden loss of power; transmission slips or shudders; difficulty shifting into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the keyless entry system can cause inconvenience and potentially lead to safety issues if the vehicle is left unlocked or unattended.
symptoms: Keyless entry system fails to work; remote entry system works intermittently; air bag lights come on at random.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various warning indicators and gauges to flicker, the vehicle to shut off, and the key to become stuck in the ignition, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Warning indicators and gauges flicker
the vehicle shuts off
the key becomes stuck in the ignition
difficulty removing the key from the ignition
and the vehicle is unable to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear defogger can cause a fire hazard due to the electrical load on the wiring connector, which can lead to a vehicle fire.
symptoms: The rear defogger stops working
and there is a burning smell or visible signs of melting or burning on the wiring connector.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, shut off, or have difficulty shifting gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
shuts off
or has difficulty shifting gears
and the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the keyless entry system can cause inconvenience and safety concerns, as the driver may not be able to enter the vehicle quickly in an emergency situation.
symptoms: The keyless entry system does not respond well
and the driver is unable to enter the vehicle through the driver's door or trunk.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Air Bag and Seat Belt Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air bag and seat belt system can cause injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The air bag light illuminates
and the seat belt indicator light illuminates
indicating a problem with the system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to become difficult to steer, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering becomes stiff or hard to turn
the steering wheel vibrates or shakes
the power steering fluid leaks
the power steering pump makes a loud noise
the vehicle wanders or drifts while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause the vehicle to become difficult to steer, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering column becomes loose or wobbly
the steering wheel vibrates or shakes
the vehicle wanders or drifts while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tie-rods can cause the vehicle to become difficult to steer, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The tie-rods fail
causing the vehicle to wander or drift while driving
the steering becomes stiff or hard to turn.
